{"key":"post-8495073","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8495073</id>\n<content>You're supposed to adjust the screw on the back of the hygrometer to calibrate it.&amp;nbsp; Just do the wet towel thing and then adjust the screw so the dial reads 99%.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Grow lights are for plants, and usually are a fairly low color temperature.&amp;nbsp; Mushrooms want a higher color temperature, with the light appearing to be bright white, almost with a bluish tint.&amp;nbsp; Get fluorescent tubes.&amp;nbsp; Look for 'natural daylight' tubes.&amp;nbsp; you can get them at lowes or any hardware store.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Mist daily a few times just before you fan it out.&amp;nbsp; High humidity, lots of fresh air, and bright light are the main pinning triggers at this point.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8495606</next>\n<prev>8494479</prev>\n<first>8494293</first>\n<last>8495629</last>\n<when>1212824682</when>\n<utime>06/07/08 10:44 AM</utime>\n</post>"}